0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"markdown-container","children":[["$","h1","h1-0",{"children":"Glossary: Automation Terminology & Definitions"}],"\n",["$","p","p-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Version"}],": 1.0 | ",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Scope"}],": 100+ terms from ancient to modern automation"]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-0",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"A"}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Actuator"}],": Device that converts control signal (electrical/hydraulic/pneumatic) into physical action (force, displacement, torque). Examples: motors, pneumatic cylinders, solenoids."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Adaptive Control"}],": Control system that adjusts parameters online to maintain performance under changing operating conditions or model uncertainty."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Autonomy Level"}],": Classification of system independence from human intervention. SAE has L0-L5 for vehicles; ISO 8373 defines robot autonomy."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Autonomy Quantification Framework (AQF)"}],": Metrics for measuring degree of autonomy; considers human involvement, system capability, situational awareness."]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-1",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"B"}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Behavioral Cloning"}],": Machine learning technique learning policy by imitating expert demonstrations; simple but suffers from distribution mismatch."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-6",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Bode Plot"}],": Frequency domain visualization showing magnitude (dB) and phase (degrees) vs frequency (Hz); used for control design and stability analysis."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-7",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Brake (fail-safe)"}],": Mechanism preventing motion if power is removed; critical for safety in collaborative robots and elevators."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-8",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Bundle Adjustment"}],": Optimization technique refining 3D reconstruction and camera poses from image matches; core SLAM method."]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-2",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"C"}],"\n",["$","p","p-9",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Chatbot (automation context)"}],": RPA application automating customer service through pre-defined conversation flows; often rule-based (not neural networks)."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-10",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Closed-Loop Control"}],": System with feedback; actual output compared to desired (reference); error signal drives corrective action. Example: cruise control."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-11",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"CMDPs (Constrained Markov Decision Processes)"}],": Reinforcement learning formulation with optimization objective AND constraint satisfaction; enables safe RL."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-12",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"CNN (Convolutional Neural Network)"}],": Deep learning architecture for vision; learns hierarchical features (edges → textures → objects) through convolution operations."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-13",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Control Barrier Functions (CBF)"}],": Mathematical certificate proving safety; if barrier function (h(s) \\geq 0), system state remains safe."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-14",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Control Theory"}],": Mathematical discipline studying feedback systems, stability, robustness; bridges continuous/discrete, linear/nonlinear systems."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-15",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Controllability"}],": Property of system; can state reach desired configuration through appropriate control inputs? Rank condition: (rank([B, AB, ..., A^{n-1}B]) = n)."]}],"\n","$L2","\n","$L3","\n","$L4","\n","$L5","\n","$L6","\n","$L7","\n","$L8","\n","$L9","\n","$La","\n","$Lb","\n","$Lc","\n","$Ld","\n","$Le","\n","$Lf","\n","$L10","\n","$L11","\n","$L12","\n","$L13","\n","$L14","\n","$L15","\n","$L16","\n","$L17","\n","$L18","\n","$L19","\n","$L1a","\n","$L1b","\n","$L1c","\n","$L1d","\n","$L1e","\n","$L1f","\n","$L20","\n","$L21","\n","$L22","\n","$L23","\n","$L24","\n","$L25","\n","$L26","\n","$L27","\n","$L28","\n","$L29","\n","$L2a","\n","$L2b","\n","$L2c","\n","$L2d","\n","$L2e","\n","$L2f","\n","$L30","\n","$L31","\n","$L32","\n","$L33","\n","$L34","\n","$L35","\n","$L36","\n","$L37","\n","$L38","\n","$L39","\n","$L3a","\n","$L3b","\n","$L3c","\n","$L3d","\n","$L3e","\n","$L3f","\n","$L40","\n","$L41","\n","$L42","\n","$L43","\n","$L44","\n","$L45","\n","$L46","\n","$L47","\n","$L48","\n","$L49","\n","$L4a","\n","$L4b","\n","$L4c","\n","$L4d","\n","$L4e","\n","$L4f","\n","$L50","\n","$L51","\n","$L52","\n","$L53","\n","$L54","\n","$L55","\n","$L56","\n","$L57","\n","$L58","\n","$L59","\n","$L5a","\n","$L5b","\n","$L5c","\n","$L5d","\n","$L5e","\n","$L5f","\n","$L60","\n","$L61","\n","$L62","\n","$L63","\n","$L64","\n","$L65","\n","$L66","\n","$L67","\n","$L68","\n","$L69","\n","$L6a","\n","$L6b","\n","$L6c","\n","$L6d","\n","$L6e","\n","$L6f","\n","$L70","\n","$L71","\n","$L72","\n","$L73","\n","$L74","\n","$L75","\n","$L76","\n","$L77","\n","$L78","\n","$L79","\n","$L7a","\n","$L7b","\n","$L7c","\n","$L7d","\n","$L7e","\n","$L7f","\n","$L80","\n","$L81","\n","$L82","\n","$L83","\n","$L84","\n","$L85","\n","$L86","\n","$L87","\n","$L88","\n","$L89","\n","$L8a","\n","$L8b","\n","$L8c","\n","$L8d","\n","$L8e","\n","$L8f","\n","$L90","\n","$L91","\n","$L92","\n","$L93","\n","$L94","\n","$L95","\n","$L96","\n","$L97","\n","$L98","\n","$L99","\n","$L9a","\n","$L9b"]}],null,"$L9c"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"sFzo4LKMJghR7e79YRpfU"}
